# RBAC & Auth System Overhaul — Implementation Plan

Safcha Dashboard ka auth, permissions, aur RBAC system fix karna hai. Deep analysis ke baad yeh major issues milein:

## Discovered Issues Summary

| # | Issue | Location | Impact |
|---|-------|----------|--------|
| 1 | `UserPermissionOverride` table → 100 users = 400+ rows, unnecessary complexity | [schema.prisma](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/prisma/schema.prisma) L810-826 | DB bloat, slow queries |
| 2 | OWNER role concept instead of ADMIN | [seed.ts](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/prisma/seed.ts), [usePermissions.ts](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/lib/hooks/usePermissions.ts) | Confusing hierarchy |
| 3 | Sidebar shows ALL items, permission checks not working properly | [Sidebar.tsx](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/components/layout/Sidebar.tsx) L147 checks `user?.role?.isSystem` | Security hole |
| 4 | [usePermissions](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/lib/hooks/usePermissions.ts#5-34) only bypasses for role name `'OWNER'` not `isSystem` generically | [usePermissions.ts](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/lib/hooks/usePermissions.ts) L12 | Non-OWNER admins blocked |
| 5 | Admin panel `redirect('/dashboard')` instead of correct slug path | [admin/layout.tsx](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/app/%5BbusinessSlug%5D/admin/layout.tsx) L17 | Broken redirect |
| 6 | Root [page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/app/page.tsx) + [select-business/page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/app/select-business/page.tsx) duplicated | [app/page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/app/page.tsx), [select-business/page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/app/select-business/page.tsx) | Code duplication |
| 7 | Server actions don't check permissions (only [getBusinessContext](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/lib/getBusinessContext.ts#5-50)) | All action files | Security hole |
| 8 | Session loads overrides unnecessarily | [session.ts](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/app/actions/auth/session.ts), [appStore.ts](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/stores/appStore.ts) | Extra data, slower load |

---

## Phase 1: DB Schema — Remove `UserPermissionOverride`, Fix Role Naming

> **Goal**: Simplify the permission model. Remove per-user overrides. Roles carry all permissions.

### Why?
Current approach: Role has permissions + each user can have override exceptions. For 100 users × 4 overrides = 400 rows in `user_permission_overrides`. This is overkill. Better approach: Admin creates roles with exact permissions. No overrides needed.

### Changes

#### [MODIFY] [schema.prisma](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/prisma/schema.prisma)
- **DELETE** the entire `UserPermissionOverride` model (L810-826)
- **REMOVE** `overrides UserPermissionOverride[]` from `BusinessUser` model (L802)
- Keep [Role](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/app/actions/adminActions.ts#13-36), `RolePermission`, `BusinessUser` as-is

#### [MODIFY] [seed.ts](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/prisma/seed.ts)
- Rename OWNER role → `ADMIN` (name field only, keep `isSystem: true`)
- This is the system-level admin role that bypasses all checks

### ✅ Checkpoint
Run `npx prisma migrate dev --name remove_overrides` and verify no errors. Check DB has no `user_permission_overrides` table.

---

## Phase 2: Fix Auth Flow — Login → Select Business → Dashboard

> **Goal**: Login ke baad user `/select-business` jaye, waha business select kare, phir dashboard dikhe.

### Current Flow
```
Login → / (root page shows business selector AGAIN)  
     → /select-business (ALSO shows business selector — duplicate)
     → /api/auth/select-business?id=xxx (sets cookie, redirects to /safcha)
```

### Desired Flow
```
Login → /select-business (single business selector page)
     → /api/auth/select-business?id=xxx (sets cookie)
     → /b/dashboard (clean, no slug in URL)
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Slug-based routing (`/safcha/products`) makes URLs longer and adds complexity. But **changing it now would require modifying 50+ files** (every page, every action). The simpler fix is to keep the slug routing but fix the flow. We can migrate slug → ID-based routing in a separate future phase.

### Changes

#### [MODIFY] [page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/app/page.tsx)
- Replace entire page with simple redirect:
```tsx
import { redirect } from 'next/navigation'
import { createClient } from '@/lib/supabase/server'

export default async function RootPage() {
    const supabase = await createClient()
    const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser()
    if (!user) redirect('/login')
    redirect('/select-business')
}
```

#### [MODIFY] [middleware.ts](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/middleware.ts)
- When user is logged in and visits `/login` → redirect to `/select-business` (not `/`)
- Line 49: change `url.pathname = '/'` to `url.pathname = '/select-business'`

### ✅ Checkpoint
Login karo → verify redirect to `/select-business`. Business select karo → verify redirect to `/{slug}` dashboard.

---

## Phase 3: Fix Permission Engine — Remove Overrides, Fix `isSystem` Check

> **Goal**: Permission system ko clean karo. `isSystem` role = full access (ADMIN). No per-user overrides.

### Changes

#### [MODIFY] [permissions.ts](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/lib/permissions.ts)
- Remove `UserPermissionOverride` import
- Remove `overrides` from [PermissionContext](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/lib/permissions.ts#3-7) type
- Remove override check logic (L19-25)
- Keep `isSystem` bypass (L14-16) — ye sahi hai

```diff
-import { Role, RolePermission, UserPermissionOverride } from '@prisma/client'
+import { Role, RolePermission } from '@prisma/client'
 
 type PermissionContext = {
     role: Role & { permissions: RolePermission[] }
-    overrides: UserPermissionOverride[]
 }
 
 export function hasPermission(
     ctx: PermissionContext,
     module: string,
     action: string
 ): boolean {
     if (ctx.role.isSystem) {
         return true
     }
 
-    const override = ctx.overrides.find(
-        (o) => o.module === module && o.action === action
-    )
-    if (override) {
-        return override.granted
-    }
-
     const rolePerm = ctx.role.permissions.find(
         (p) => p.module === module && p.action === action
     )
     return !!rolePerm
 }
```

#### [MODIFY] [usePermissions.ts](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/lib/hooks/usePermissions.ts)
- Replace `user.role.isSystem && user.role.name === 'OWNER'` with just `user.role.isSystem`
- Remove overrides check entirely

```diff
 const can = (module: string, action: string): boolean => {
     if (!user) return false
 
-    if (user.role.isSystem && user.role.name === 'OWNER') {
+    if (user.role.isSystem) {
         return true
     }
 
-    const override = user.overrides.find(...)
-    if (override) { return override.granted }
-
     const rolePerm = user.role.permissions.find(
         (p: any) => p.module === module && p.action === action
     )
     return !!rolePerm
 }
```

#### [MODIFY] [getBusinessContext.ts](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/lib/getBusinessContext.ts)
- Remove `overrides: true` from include (L32)
- Remove `overrides` from return object (L47)

#### [MODIFY] [session.ts](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/app/actions/auth/session.ts)
- Remove `overrides: true` from include (L21)
- Remove `overrides:` mapping from return object (L41-45)

#### [MODIFY] [appStore.ts](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/stores/appStore.ts)
- Remove `overrides: any[]` from User interface (L13)

### ✅ Checkpoint
App ko chalao. Login karo. Dashboard load hona chahiye bina error ke. Console me koi `overrides` related error nahi hona chahiye.

