## Phase 4: Fix Sidebar — Permission-Based Item Filtering

> **Goal**: Sidebar me sirf woh items dikhen jo user ki role permissions me hain. Admin Panel sirf `isSystem` roles ko dikhe.

### Current Problem
[Sidebar.tsx](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/components/layout/Sidebar.tsx) line 147: `if ((item as any).adminOnly && !user?.role?.isSystem) return null;`
This checks `adminOnly` flag AND `isSystem` — but line 149 also checks [can()](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/lib/hooks/usePermissions.ts#8-31). The issue is if `user` is null (loading state), everything gets hidden.

### Changes

#### [MODIFY] [Sidebar.tsx](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/safcha%20dash%202/safcha-dashboard/components/layout/Sidebar.tsx)
- Ensure `adminOnly` check uses `user?.role?.isSystem` correctly
- Show loading state if user is null instead of empty sidebar
- Remove `overrides` dependency (already removed from store in Phase 3)

```diff
 {navigation.map((item: any) => {
+  // Don't render anything until user is loaded
+  if (!user) return null;
+  
   // Hide admin-only items from non-system roles
-  if ((item as any).adminOnly && !user?.role?.isSystem) return null;
+  if (item.adminOnly && !user.role.isSystem) return null;
   // Hide item if user doesn't have permission
   if (!can(item.permission.module, item.permission.action)) return null;
```

Add a loading skeleton at the top of the sidebar when user is null:

```tsx
{!user && (
  <div className="px-3 space-y-2">
    {[...Array(6)].map((_, i) => (
      <div key={i} className="h-10 rounded-lg bg-white/5 animate-pulse" />
    ))}
  </div>
)}
```

### ✅ Checkpoint
Non-admin user se login karo. Sidebar me sirf allowed modules dikhen. Admin Panel link na dikhe. Admin se login karo → sab dikhe.

